% recipient data
\recipient{HR CNAG-CRG}{C/  Dr. Aiguader 88\\
	08003 Barcelona\\Spain}
\date{March 30, 2018}
\opening{Dear Sirs,}
\closing{Sincerely yours,}
\enclosure[Attached]{curriculum vit\ae{}}          % use an optional argument to use a string other than "Enclosure", or redefine \enclname
\makelettertitle

I would like to apply for the position of Senior Postdoc in Rare Disease Genomics at CNAG-CRG in Barcelona.

First of all, I have finished medical studies and worked for two years as a university teacher in pathophysiology department in Cracow, which gives me a rather good background for projects dealing with human diseases. Moreover, my PhD in human genetics at Karolinska, Sweden was about genetics of cancers. During that time I successively have moved from genetics wet lab to Sanger DNA sequencing, then the sequence assembly and analysis.   
After that I have worked for seven years as in bioinformatics support in US and UK, gaining experience starting from Unix/Linux system administration, through software maintenance and participation in various research projects. While my skills in that ares certainly need an update, I have supported following core facilities/research groups: crystallography, NMR, protein mass spectography, molecular modeling.   

In the last years working in the groups of respectively Dr H. Himmelsbauer’s,  Dr R. Guigo’s, Dr C. Notredame’s  and Dr I. Gut at CRG/CNAG I have mastered programs a number of used by the Next Generation Sequencing/genome annotation as well as the Sun Grid Engine clustering software used here.  
With Dr Notredame we started collaboration with Dr Spaeth from Institute Pasteur, Paris, France, and subsequently with Dr Figueiredo from U.of Lisboa, Portugal, working on Leishmania and Trypanosoma parasites respectively. For these projects I have performed Leishmania genome (ca 32Mbp) assembly, SNP calling, genome comparisons and detection of trans-spliced gene ends using RNASeq.  
Also during four years I was involved in EU collaborative Quantomics project, where our part was to improve annotation in particular of lncRNAs in several farm animals (cows, chicken, etc.), giving me insights into non-human vertebrate genomes. My last position required creation of analytic pipelines to verify mutations in the Pan-Cancer data.
My main research interests include genome assembly, genome annotation, RNASeq analysis and genome annotation, but I would like to refresh my disease gene(s) hunting skills.


Please refer to the accompanying CV for more detailed information regarding my abilities and skill sets. 



\makeletterclosing


